WHAT IS pwned-checker.pl ?
==================
It is a simple script to ask you for your passwords and check 
the database of https://haveibeenpwned.com/Passwords if it was
disclosed


FEATURES
========
- allowes to show passwords on entry (by default it doesn't)
- counts and shows matched passwords, but only as sha1 hash


SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS
=====================
- Perl 5.28.1 or higher (not tested older versions)


DOCUMENTATION
=============
First go to https://haveibeenpwned.com/Passwords and download a
SHA1 archive. If you copied it to your local drive extract it.
You can use https://www.7-zip.org/ for this purpose.
Start pwned-checker.pl with the local text file as argument (mandatory)

./pwned-checker.pl pwned-passwords-sha1-ordered-*-v4.txt [--show-passwords]

Available options:

	File.txt
		Mandatory! File to sha1 hashed password list of
		https://haveibeenpwned.com/Passwords

	--show-passwords
		Optionally show passwords while entering on shell
		(Disabled by default)


